OL,6,F"And for my part in that, I'm truly
OL,7,Fsorry that I've been associated with
OL,8,Fthis. I'm truly sorry for that."
OL,10,FChairman Sir Wyn Williams interjected:
OL,11,F"I think the point, Mr Williams, is at
OL,12,Fa moment in time, namely 2014, when on
OL,13,Fany sensible reading of Mr Clarke's
OL,14,Fadvice from July 2013, there was a
OL,15,Fproblem about Mr Jenkins's evidence,
OL,16,Fthe Post Office and you personally
OL,17,Fappeared to still be asserting to the
OL,18,Fworld that the conviction was safe,
OL,19,Famongst other things, because expert
OL,20,Fevidence had been called and the jury,
OL,21,Fby inference, must have accepted it.
